column22: There are now only a few more questions left! Please press space to continue.

During the task, you first learned image pairs. For example, you first learned the book was paired with the woman. Later, you decided whether two images weighed more than a small dog. In this small dog task, you saw an image you had already learned (e.g., the book) with a new image (e.g., the alpaca).
column23: IN GENERAL, during the small dog task, when you saw an old image with a new pair, did you recall the earlier image pair (e.g., the woman)? Press 0 on your keyboard if you did not recall the earlier image pair, press 1 if you were actively trying to recall the earlier image pair, press 2 if the earlier image pair popped into mind without you trying.

column22: Did you recall the earlier image pair when you FIRST saw the new pair, during the arrow task, or both?
column23: Press 1 if you recalled the earlier image pair when you first encountered  the new pair. Press 2 if you mostly recalled the earlier image pair during the arrow task. Press 3 if the answer is both. Press 0 if you did not think of the image pair.

column22: If you were thinking about the earlier image pair during the arrow task, how much of the arrow task were you thinking about it? Let each number below indicate a percentage and round to the nearest tenth of a percentage.. Drag the blue triangle left and right and once you have settled on a response, press 'enter' on your keyboard.
